{{Infobox magazine | title = Croc | logo = | logo_size = | image_file = Croc magazines.jpg | image_size = <!-- (defaults to user thumbnail size if no size is stated) --> | image_alt = A pile of issues of ''Croc'' | image_caption = | editor = Pierre Huet | editor_title = Editor in Chief | previous_editor = | staff_writer = | photographer = | category = Comics, Humour | frequency = Monthly | circulation = | publisher = Éditions Ludcom | founder = [[Jacques Hurtubise (cartoonist)|Jacques Hurtubise]] | founded = | firstdate = October 1979 <!-- {{Start date|year|month|day}} --> | finaldate = April 1995 | company = | country = Canada | based = [[Montreal]] | language = French | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | issn = 0226-6083 | oclc = }} '''''Croc''''' was a [[French language|French-language]] humour magazine published monthly in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], Canada from 1979 until 1995.<ref name=tsun>{{cite news|author1=Isabella Maher|title=Former staff of defunct Que. humour magazine talk Charlie Hebdo|url=http://www.torontosun.com/2015/01/10/former-staff-of-defunct-que-humour-magazine-talk-charlie-hebdo|accessdate=November 7, 2015|work=Toronto Sun|date=January 10, 2015|location=Montreal}}</ref>
==Publication history== ''Croc'' ("Fang" in French)<ref name="CJC-Spalding"/> was begun in October 1979 by Jacques Hurtubise, Hélène Fleury, and Roch Côté, with the help of an $80,000 grant from the ''ministère des Affaires culturelles du Québec'' ("Québec Ministry of Cultural Affairs"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thecanadianencyclopedia.com/articles/emc/ministere-des-affaires-culturelles-du-quebec|title=Ministère des Affaires culturelles du Québec|accessdate=January 13, 2011|first=Gilles|last=Potvin|work=The Canadian Encyclopedia}}</ref>).<ref name="BTF-QC-QuebecMarket"/> It printed the work of many leading [[cartoonist]]s of the era, many of whom were able to launch their careers through the magazine's help,<ref name="CanEncFrenchComicStrips"/> including animator [[Claude Cloutier]].<ref name=blog>{{cite web|url=http://blog.nfb.ca/blog/2015/07/31/frame-x-frame-claude-cloutier/|title=Frame x Frame: Meet Filmmaker Claude Cloutier (interview)|date=31 July 2015|work=NFB.ca Blog|publisher=National Film Board of Canada|accessdate=2 December 2015}}</ref>
''Croc'' begat another magazine, ''Titanic'', dedicated entirely to comics.<ref name="BTF-QC-QuebecMarket" /> Croc's publishers briefly distributed [[Mad (magazine)#Past foreign editions|a localised edition of MAD magazine]] from 1991-1992, which adapted and translated existing "MAD" back articles by replacing [[New York City]] references to [[Montréal]] contexts.
For a number of reasons, ''Croc'' ceased publication in April 1995<ref name=tsun/> after 189 issues.
